cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision, specifically on improving the performance of convolutional networks for image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses regularization techniques and optimization strategies, which are common topics in machine learning and deep learning research, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category. The use of factorized convolutions and computational efficiency also suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents benchmark results on the ILSVRC 2012 classification challenge, which is a widely recognized computer vision competition, indicating that cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible sub-category.
